Description of adult male. Total body length 0.96 mm ; paratypes 0.91–0.97 mm . Body (
Fig. 16
) elongate, heavily chitinised and perforated, 10.2 times as long as wide, and thoracomeres and pleomeres telescoping into each other to varying degrees. In lateral view, pleomeres wider than thoracomeres. Head 1.2 times as long as wide, 23.3 % longer than first 2 thoracomeres combined.
